            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"服药说明，例如 '饭前半小时服用'、'体温>38.5℃时服用'\"\n          },\n          \"indication\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"用药指征（针对哪个症状/诊断），可写主诊断 ICD-10 或自由文本\"\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"non_drug_advice\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"description\": \"非药物医嘱（生活方式/饮食/复诊）\",\n      \"items\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n    },\n    \"clinical_reasoning\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"用药决策的临床思路。必须显式覆盖：(1) 为什么开这些药；(2) 与病人特殊情况（年龄/过敏/肝肾功能/合并用药）的匹配性；(3) 预期监测/复诊节点。\"\n    },\n    \"explicit_avoidance\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"description\": \"显式说明本次刻意避免使用的药物/方案及原因。例如：[{drug_or_class: '抗生素', reason: '病毒性感染无指征'}]。这是验证 agent 是否理解临床决策边界的关键字段。\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": [\"drug_or_class\", \"reason\"],\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"drug_or_class\": {\"type\": \"string\"},\n          \"reason\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"follow_up\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"description\": \"随访计划\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"next_visit_days\": {\"type\": \"number\"},\n        \"red_flags\": {\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"description\": \"需要立即返诊的危险征兆\",\n          \"items\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_1780196597044_frxv3q4nj0j","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-4.7-opus","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Looking at this patient case: a 68-year-old woman presenting with a two-day cough, sputum production, and one day of fever up to 38°C, diagnosed with community-acquired pneumonia. She weighs 54kg and is 158cm tall, with significant comorbidities including end-stage renal disease.\n\nShe's on maintenance hemodialysis three times weekly (Monday/Wednesday/Friday), with her last session on Friday, May 29th. Her kidney function is severely compromised with an eGFR of 6 and creatinine clearance of 8. She also has hypertension and an arteriovenous fistula in her right upper arm. She has a documented penicillin allergy causing generalized urticaria.\n\nHer current medications include valsartan 80mg daily, hydrochlorothiazide 12.5mg daily, and recombinant erythropoietin 10,000 units weekly. Vital signs show elevated blood pressure at 152/62, current temperature of 37.1°C (though she had 38°C yesterday), oxygen saturation 95%, and respiratory rate 18. Lab work reveals normal WBC at 5.41 but elevated neutrophils at 81.9% and low lymphocytes at 8.2%, with elevated CRP at 56 and procalcitonin at 0.21—relatively low but doesn't completely rule out bacterial infection. Creatinine is 786 as expected for a dialysis patient, and hemoglobin is normal at 117. Imaging shows right middle lobe consolidation consistent with lobar pneumonia, bilateral interstitial changes, and left lower lobe bronchitis.\n\nThis is a typical community-acquired pneumonia case in an elderly dialysis patient, and empiric antibiotic therapy needs to be selected carefully given her penicillin allergy and renal status.\n\nFor antibiotic selection, I'm considering her CURB-65 score which comes to about 1-2 points (age 68 and elevated BUN from dialysis), putting her in the mild-to-moderate range. Given she's a dialysis patient with a moderate penicillin allergy (non-anaphylactic but systemic urticaria), I should avoid penicillins and use caution with cephalosporins. Respiratory fluoroquinolones like moxifloxacin are a good option here—they cover pneumococcus and atypical pathogens well, don't require renal dose adjustment since they're hepatically metabolized, though I need to monitor for QT prolongation. Levofloxacin is another viable alternative.\n\nGiven the outpatient setting and her dialysis status, I'm leaning toward either moxifloxacin 400mg daily or levofloxacin adjusted for her severely reduced renal function—750mg as a loading dose followed by 500mg every 48 hours, timed after dialysis. Macrolides like azithromycin don't need dose adjustment in dialysis patients either. While hospitalization would be more appropriate for a dialysis patient with lobar pneumonia, if outpatient management is being pursued, moxifloxacin monotherapy seems like the most practical choice given her medication profile and allergy history.\n\nFor symptom management, her current temperature isn't high enough to warrant antipyretics, but I'd add a mucolytic agent like ambroxol 30mg three times daily to help with her cough and sputum production—both are safe in dialysis patients. I should avoid penicillins and cephalosporins due to her allergy history, aminoglycosides because of nephrotoxicity concerns, and vancomycin since there's no indication for empiric MRSA coverage. After dialysis, I'd reassess her clinical response. Writing prescription JSON... 对症用氨溴索30mg三次日常口服化痰，透析患者安全无需调量。评估合并用药时，缬沙坦和氢氯噻嗪与莫西沙星无显著相互作用，但需注意氢氯噻嗪可能引起低钾加重QT延长，建议透析前复查电解质；莫西沙星本身可延长QT间期，在老年女性和透析患者中风险更高，所以这次透析时要复查钾、镁、钙水平，如条件允许也要复查心电图QTc。随访计划是3天后复诊评估症状改善情况，透析时监测电解质和肝肾功能，若出现气促、胸痛、咯血、血氧饱和度下降或意识改变需立即就诊。\n\n需要避免青霉素类、头孢菌素类、氨基糖苷类和NSAIDs。莫西沙星相比其他选择更合适——大环内酯单药对肺炎链球菌耐药率高不适合大叶性肺炎，万古霉素无MRSA指征，左氧氟沙星在透析患者需复杂调量。还要提醒患者莫西沙星需与多价阳离子间隔服用，因为ESRD患者常用磷结合剂如钙剂或司维拉姆。","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":33109,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1611166a-0d7e-40d1-a804-e8a407dff982","uuid":"62e2902f-8374-4372-be16-5501e6cfdb8c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_1780196597044_frxv3q4nj0j","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-4.7-opus","content":[{"type":"text","text":"我已经获取到病人的 EMR 和当前接诊信息。让我分析临床情况：\n\n**关键临床要点：**\n- 68岁女性，54kg，**ESRD 维持性血液透析**（eGFR 6, CrCl 8, 周一/三/五透析）\n- 主诊断：J18.1 大叶性肺炎（右肺中叶实变 + CRP 56 + N% 81.9% + 1天前发热38℃）\n- 青霉素**中度过敏**史（2008年全身荨麻疹）\n- 当前用药：缬沙坦、氢氯噻嗪、重组EPO\n\n**治疗决策：莫西沙星单药 + 氨溴索化痰**\n\n让我提交处方："}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":33109,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1611166a-0d7e-40d1-a804-e8a407dff982","uuid":"d1dd142a-a1ce-4987-8b83-0b49a20d6921"}
